  <programme start="20260307163400 +0100" stop="20260307174000 +0100" channel="MEZZO">
    <title lang="pl">Jean-Yves Thibaudet, San Francisco Symphony Orchestra, Esa-Pekka Salonen: Scriabin - Prometheus</title>
    <desc lang="pl">San Francisco Symphony Orchestra, Esa-Pekka Salonen (conductor) Jean-Yves Thibaudet (piano) Mathilde Laurent (perfumer) Alexander Scriabin 1872 - 1915 Prometheus, The Poem of Fire Alexander Scriabin's symphonic poem 'Prometheus, The Poem of Fire' celebrates synesthesia and cosmic unity. Devised by San Francisco Symphony Music Director Esa-Pekka Salonen, pianist Jean-Yves Thibaudet, and Cartier in-house perfumer Mathilde Laurent, the San Francisco Symphony and Cartier present a multisensory production of 'Prometheus'. This collaborative world premiere combines dynamic musical and light performance with olfactory curation, subsuming audiences in Scriabin's creative vision more than a century after the piece of total art was composed. Directed by Sébastien Glas San Francisco, Davies Symphony Hall, 3 mars 2024.</desc>
    <credits>
      <director>Sébastien Glas</director>
    </credits>
    <date>2024</date>
    <category lang="pl">classical concert</category>
    <icon src="https://ptv-prod.wpcdn.pl/media/akpa4984469.jpg" />
